---
/**
 * Privacy Policy — scoped to this website (owner decision). Accurate to the
 * built site: no cookies, no analytics, no forms, self-hosted fonts, no
 * third-party embeds. Standard Australian small-business framing (Privacy Act
 * 1988 / APPs). Not legal advice.
 */
import LegalPage from '../layouts/LegalPage.astro';
import Email from '../components/Email.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.ts';
---

<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Beacon Diagnostics handles information in connection with this website."
  lastUpdated="10 July 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Beacon Diagnostics handles information in
    connection with this website (beacondiagnostics.com.au). We are committed to
    protecting your privacy and handle personal information in line with the
    Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles.
  </p>

  <h2>Information this website collects</h2>
  <p>
    This website does not use cookies, analytics, or tracking technologies, and
    it does not contain any forms. It does not collect personal information from
    you as you browse.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting and server logs</h2>
  <p>
    This site is hosted on GitHub Pages. As with most web hosting, our hosting
    provider may automatically process standard technical information — such as
    your IP address, browser type, and the date and time of requests — for the
    purpose of serving and securing the website. That information is handled
    under the hosting provider&rsquo;s own privacy terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Information you provide directly</h2>
  <p>
    If you contact us by email or telephone, we receive the information you
    choose to provide — such as your name, contact details, and the content of
    your message. We use this only to respond to you and to provide our
    services. We do not sell or rent your information, and we do not share it
    except where necessary to provide a service you have requested or where
    required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Holding and securing information</h2>
  <p>
    We keep personal information only for as long as it is needed for the
    purpose it was provided, and take reasonable steps to keep it secure.
  </p>

  <h2>Access and correction</h2>
  <p>
    You may request access to, or correction of, any personal information we
    hold about you by contacting us using the details below.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The current version is always
    the one published on this page, with the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date
    shown above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Email: <Email /><br />
    Phone: {SITE.phone} ({SITE.phoneMnemonic})
  </p>
</LegalPage>
